                            <comment id="12838282" author="jake.mannix" created="Thu, 25 Feb 2010 10:08:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch has newly modified unit tests to test the symmetric case, and they pass (both for LanczosSolver and DistributedLanczosSolver).  This has not been tested on large sparse symmetric matrices for performance yet, as I don&apos;t have any such data sets to try it out on right now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12839869" author="jake.mannix" created="Mon, 1 Mar 2010 21:32:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hope we get this release out soon, I&apos;ve got a giant pile of code burning a hole in my laptop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current patch fixes this ticket as well as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-312&quot; title=&quot;DistributedRowMatrix iterateAll() and iterate() don&amp;#39;t work on multi-part SequenceFiles&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-312&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-312&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-313&quot; title=&quot;DistributedRowMatrix needs times(Vector) implementation as M/R job&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-313&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-313&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-314&quot; title=&quot;DistributedRowMatrix needs a sparse DistributedRowMatrix times(DistributedRowMatrix other) implementation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (unit tests included)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
